HEADWORD: Rep-silver
<hw>Rep"-sil`ver</hw> <pr>(r?p"s?l`v?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Reap</er>.]</ety> <def>Money anciently paid by servile tenants to
their lord, in lieu of the customary service of reaping his corn or
grain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reptant</ent>⟦br⟧
